  "firstAcquaintance": "Inlia grasped the Holy Lance and reversed the demon power within her, returning to her youth. Her memories regressed along with her body.",
  "personality": "A royal knight raised by the kingdom, she upholds the spirit of chivalry. Strict yet retaining the youthful innocence of a young girl.",
  "like": "Weapons, sweets, girly accessories",
  "familiarData": "Inlia accidentally grasped the Holy Lance, which reversed the demonic power within her and brought her back to her last turning point, freeing her body from demonic corruption. As a result, she reverted to her younger self before she ever reached the frontlines.\nInlia's demonic power came from her promise to Princess Oru Baid. With the demon power gone, her memories also rewound to the past. She only remembers being in the royal city not long ago, then suddenly finding herself in demon territory.\nHer memories of Princess Oru Baid stopped several years ago. The current Princess Oru Baid seems familiar to her, but she cannot recognize who she is.\nThe present Inlia possesses the innocence and dreams of her past, and her attitude toward the demon race has softened considerably. However, her hatred toward slave owners has only grown deeper, and her animosity toward a certain honorary demon citizen is bone-deep. Even without her memories, she still shows hostility toward that particular person.\n\nInlia cannot recall her original experiences, so the current her can be said to be an Inlia walking a completely different path.",
